Data from the World Database on Protected Areas (WDPA) were used to identify the PAs in China with areas greater than 4.3Â km at the equator that were suitable for analysis in this study (
 http://www.protectedplanet.net/). We classified 642 Chinese PAs into five groups based on the IUCN protected area categories: Category Ia, strict nature reserve; Category II, national park; Category IV, habitat/species management area; Category V, protected landscape/seascape; and Category VI, protected area with sustainable use of natural resources. Based on WDPA database, there are no PAs belonging to Category Ib (wilderness area) and Category III (natural monument or feature; 
 http://www.protectedplanet.net/).
